This paper deals with the problem of manipulating videos, specifically inserting one video into another. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves analyzing and processing visual data. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks and adversarial learning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the handling of complex backgrounds, which could fall under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves synthesizing fake training pairs, which could also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
